This location is my go-to Shake Shack since it opened! When you walk in, you notice that your never going to get a seat. You get in line, assuming there is going to be a seat when you get out of line. If you never get a seat, I recommend taking the food out, and bringing it to Colombia University across the street from this Shake Shack. In Colombia University, you can sit on one of the benches they have, and eat there! Shake Shack Food is really, really good! Some people say that it just looks different, and taste the same as any other French fry. These people are Right, and Wrong. The French fries may taste slightly different from the others, but it doesn't taste that different. All that matters, is that the fries are good (and that they are not not McDonald's fries.) The Hot Dogs are good as well, but make sure to eat them over you table, so you don't get the oil that drips from the sausage on your clothes (the hot dog is very oily.) The shakes are also really good! I would recommend getting one of the Featured shakes, they always taste good! The service is ok 👌. The staff do their job, and that's what matters most. The atmosphere is good. There are these pictures that represent Shake Shack on the walls, which is fun. It is pretty loud, because this Shake Shack is packed, most of the time.

If I’m going to each fast food, it’s going to be ShakeShake! The wait time is a big longer than your typical fast food joint, since they make each burger to order... but believe me... it’s well worth the wait. The Smoke Shake is my fave.
